To qualify for a license, an applicant shall:
Be of good moral character;
Demonstrate oral and written competency in the English language as required by the Board;
Be at least 18 years old; and
Be a graduate of a physician assistant training program approved by the Board; or
Have passed the physician assistant national certifying examination administered by the National Commission on Certification of Physician Assistants prior to 1986, maintained all continuing education and recertification requirements, and been in continuous practice since passage of the examination.
